cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper deals with computer vision and machine learning techniques for spatiotemporal action localization in videos. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also presents a unified CNN architecture, which involves optimization and training of the neural network, indicating that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper uses deep learning techniques to extract temporal and spatial information, which could also place it in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with video processing, which could place it in cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper involves optimization of the neural network, which could also place it in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
